description.value: Sharply carinated pottery bowl, hand-made, with a red-slipped exterior, the slip worn off towards the base. Prior to the appliaction of the slip six groups of five shallow lines were scored almost vertically on the pot from immediately below the rim past the carination. At the carination is a single oval boss pierced horizontally. There is a shallow groove around the vessel immediately below the plain rim. A single vertical crack on the upper part of the body is flanked by a pair of repair holes.

description.value: Black-topped red ware bowl with an inverted plain rim and a rounded base; orangey-brown fabric, black and burnished on the exterior above the carination and the interior surface, deeply incised crisscross lines on the exterior surface below the carination extending across the base. Handmade. The body surface has been pierced six times from the exterior to produce a series of conical mending holes; with four holes along part of the rim and two holes beneath those in the body. Complete but reconstructed with small chips on the rim.
